		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kevin Townsend]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Endpoint Security]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Malware & Threats]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[malware]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[MSHTA]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.securityweek.com/?p=46509</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Attackers are increasingly abusing Microsoft’s decades-old MSHTA utility to stealthily deliver stealers, loaders, and persistent malware through phishing, fake software downloads, and LOLBIN-based attack chains.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.securityweek.com/legacy-windows-tool-mshta-fuels-surge-in-silent-malware-attacks/">Legacy Windows Tool MSHTA Fuels Surge in Silent Malware Attacks</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.securityweek.com">SecurityWeek</a>.</p>
]]></description>
		
		
		
